Hi {{first_name}},

I’m sharing Pancake Robot, a new character-driven kids music project built around breakfast, robots, and silly movement songs. The core audience is 4-7, but the goal is parent-tolerable kindie: bright hooks, simple words, no shame/scary themes, and a chorus kids can sing by the second listen.

The new track, {{song_title}}, is built around {{specific_hook}}. It includes a kid-copyable sound/action cue and a short visual clip if useful.

Private listen: {{private_link}}
Public release date: {{release_date}}
Assets: {{asset_link}}

Worth a listen if you’re looking for upbeat, safe, slightly weird family music.

KC
